description: BJP councillor Sunder Singh Tanwar secured a seat on the Municipal Corporation of Delhi's standing committee following withdrawals by AAP and Congress. With BJP now holding a majority in the committee, further confrontations are anticipated as AAP dominates the House, potentially postponing formal approvals.

This action was taken following a special court's directive based on activist Snehamayi Krishna's complaint. A petition seeks CBI involvement due to the significant financial implications.

description: The Uttarakhand government is preparing a stringent land purchase law to control large-scale acquisitions in hilly regions by non-residents. This new legislation aims to identify and reclaim illegally acquired land, ensuring compliance with existing norms. The focus is on preventing misuse of regulations for personal gain while supporting genuine investors.
title: In bid to check outsider influx, U'khand to make buying of land tougher

description: Nishikant Dubey of BJP and TMC's Mahua Moitra, who had a previous clash over cash-for-query charges resulting in Moitra's expulsion from Lok Sabha, are now on the same parliamentary standing committee on communications and information technology. Dubey chairs the committee with members including Kangana Ranaut of BJP, Jaya Bachchan of SP, and music composer Ilaiyaraja.
title: Mahua & Kangana members of House panel led by Nishikant

description: The Uttarakhand government is preparing a stringent land purchase law to control large-scale acquisitions in hilly regions by non-residents. description: The Centre has raised minimum wage rates for unorganised sector workers through a revision of the variable dearness allowance. Effective from Oct 1, these new rates are categorised by skill levels and geographical areas. This move is intended to help workers cope with increasing living costs.
title: Minimum wages for unorganised sector to rise as variable DA up
Car-in-truck, high-speed chase & gunshots in ATM gang endgame

description: The Israeli military and Hezbollah engaged in strikes on Friday. Hezbollah targeted Safed in northern Israel with rockets, causing property damage but no injuries. This was a response to an earlier Israeli airstrike on Hezbollah’s southern Beirut headquarters, which resulted in casualties and destruction. The conflict has led to a humanitarian crisis with many displaced.
title: Hezbollah hits back at Israel following IDF airstrikes on Beirut

description: BJP councillor Sunder Singh Tanwar secured a seat on the Municipal Corporation of Delhi's standing committee following withdrawals by AAP and Congress. With BJP now holding a majority in the committee, further confrontations are anticipated as AAP dominates the House, potentially postponing formal approvals.
title: BJP takes MCD panelseat as AAP pulls out
Man digs up gory past: Mother, brothers killed & buried dad 30 years ago
Will examine charges of interference in judicial system in Chandigarh: SC

description: Bangladesh's interim government chief adviser Mohammad Yunus met ICC prosecutor Karim AA Khan to discuss procedures for trying crimes against humanity. This has intensified speculation about plans to extradite ousted PM Sheikh Hasina, accused in relation to violent protests. Despite an extradition treaty, India may block her handover.
title: Yunus sparks Hasina extradition buzz after talks with ICC lawyer

description: Bibek Debroy has resigned as chancellor of Gokhale Institute of Politics and Economics in Pune on moral grounds. This comes after the Bombay High Court allowed Ajit Ranade to remain as vice-chancellor until October 7, despite Debroy’s earlier order for his removal. The court’s decision challenges Debroy’s authority.
title: Ranade row: Bibek Debroy quits as chancellor of Gokhale Institute

description: The Karnataka Lokayukta has filed an FIR against Chief Minister Siddaramaiah, his wife, and brother-in-law over allegations of corruption and land grabbing tied to the Mysore Urban Development Authority land allotment case. This action was taken following a special court's directive based on activist Snehamayi Krishna's complaint. A petition seeks CBI involvement due to the significant financial implications.
title: Karnataka Lokayukta files FIR against CM Siddaramaiah for graft case

description: The Israeli military executed a large-scale airstrike on Hezbollah’s headquarters in southern Beirut, targeting leader Hassan Nasrallah. The bombardment destroyed multiple buildings and caused significant damage. Lebanon reported two deaths and 76 injuries. Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu cut short his US visit to address the situation, intensifying regional tensions.
title: Israel's Beirut airstrike aimed to assassinate Hezbollah chief Nasrallah

description: The Supreme Court has reprimanded the Commission of Air Quality Management for its failure to address stubble burning in Punjab and Haryana, leading to severe winter air pollution in Delhi. Despite the CAQM Act providing extensive powers, no effective measures have been implemented. The court calls for concrete actions and accountability from officials.
title: 'All in the air': SC flays CAQM 'inaction' on fires
NIA raids 7 places in Reasi bus attack case

description: At least 64 people have been killed in renewed violence between Pashtun Sunni and Shia tribes in Pakistan's Kurram district, despite a ceasefire signed last month. The clashes began over land disputes and have led to road closures, food shortages, and school shutdowns in the region bordering Afghanistan. Governor Faisal Karim Kundi of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province said dozens on either side were wounded in the fighting
title: 64 killed in a week as Pak's Khyber tribal truce collapses
Tory leadership contender pledges UK visa ban if India doesn't accept returns
NC-Cong & PDP trying to revive J&K’s era of violence: Nadda

description: Cleveland Browns' Myles Garrett is dealing with foot, Achilles, and thigh injuries but plans to play against the Las Vegas Raiders on Sunday. The reigning Defensive Player of the Year hasn't missed a game since Week 4 of 2022. Despite reduced performance due to injuries, Garrett's determination remains strong as he prepares for the upcoming match.
title: Myles Garrett brushes off injuries, ready for raiders

description: Rey Mysterio acknowledges the crucial role his wife Angie Gutiérrez played in his wrestling career. Married since 1996, Angie initially pursued medicine but later turned to entrepreneurship and acting. They have two children: Dominik, who is also in WWE, and Aalyah, who is studying medicine.
title: Who is Rey Mysterio's wife? Exploring personal life of master of 619

description: A wall collapse near Ujjain's Mahakal temple due to heavy rains resulted in two fatalities and two injuries. The district administration announced compensation for the victims' families. Rescue efforts were swiftly carried out, and the injured were transferred to Indore for further medical attention.
title: 2 killed, two injured in wall collapse near Mahakal temple

description: Assam Chief Minister Himanta Biswa Sarma addressed the demographic issue in Jharkhand, stating that the National Register of Citizens (NRC) will be implemented and those not listed will be sent to Bangladesh. ​"This will be our policy. Everyone will get the opportunity to present their side when NRC is done," he added.
title: 'NRC will be done': Assam CM on Jharkhand's demographic issue

description: Anna Shinde, father of Akshay Shinde who was accused in the Badlapur sexual assault case, is seeking police protection for his family due to threats received after his son's death. Akshay was shot dead while in police custody. Anna alleges it was a conspiracy and has requested a court-monitored investigation into the incident.
title: Father of Badlapur accused seeks police protection, writes to Amit Shah

description: A coalition of 131 CEOs from different countries, including India, managed to cut their companies' emissions by 10% while increasing revenues by 18% from 2019 to 2022. This was reported by the World Economic Forum during the UN General Assembly in New York, showcasing that economic growth and climate action can be compatible.
title: CEOs for climate action alliance cut emissions while boosting revenues: WEF

description: Mumbai Police have called in the CEO of BookMyShow's parent company and technical head over allegations of black-marketing Coldplay concert tickets. This action follows complaints about ticket sales glitches and counterfeit tickets. BookMyShow, the authorized ticketing partner, has condemned scalping and advised fans to buy only from official sources for genuine tickets.
title: Coldplay tickets row: Police summons CEO of BookMyShow parent company

description: India is ramping up its artillery capabilities along the China frontier by adding more long-range precision firepower. The Army will induct 100 K-9 Vajra self-propelled guns, additional Dhanush howitzers, Sharang guns, and Pinaka rocket systems. Efforts are also being made to boost indigenous ammunition production to address global supply chain disruptions.
title: India inducting more long-range firepower & indigenising ammo amid border row with China

description: Donald Trump met Ukraine President Volodymyr Zelenskyy in New York, claiming he could end the Russia-Ukraine war if elected. Kamala Harris warned that Trump's plan might force Ukraine to give up territory. The meeting highlights Zelenskyy's careful maneuvering within US political dynamics and his need to hedge bets on the election outcome.
title: Trump tells Zelenskyy he will forge peace with Russia; Kamala says he will force Ukraine to surrender

description: Lalit Modi has warned investors about the ECB's revenue projections for The Hundred tournament. The ECB plans to sell stakes in its eight teams. Modi criticized these projections, particularly those from international markets, and questioned the high valuations of the teams, calling it a misleading effort.
title: 'ECB trying to fool people': Modi cautions IPL owners

description: In Hathras, Uttar Pradesh, a Class 2 boy was allegedly killed as part of a human sacrifice ritual at his school. The father claims he was misled by the school authorities about his son's death. Five people, including the school's director and three teachers, have been arrested. Authorities are investigating the illegal operation of the school's hostel.
title: 'Neck broken ...': Father of Class 2 boy killed in 'human sacrifice'

description: A group of protestors demonstrated outside the United Nations headquarters in New York against Bangladesh chief adviser Prof Muhammad Yunus, accusing him of illegally seizing power and inciting violence. They called for his resignation, highlighting attacks on minorities and urging global leaders to intervene for peace in Bangladesh.
title: 'Hindu killer': Protest in New York against Bangladesh interim chief Yunus

description: WWE has announced a two-night SummerSlam event in New Jersey for August 2025. Fans are excited about the possibility of John Cena winning his record-breaking 17th World Championship during this event, which aligns with his 'Farewell Tour'. The timing and scale of SummerSlam make it an ideal occasion for this historic milestone.
title: SummerSlam 2025: Is John Cena winning his 17th World Title in the event?

description: Congress president Mallikarjun Kharge dismissed BJP's demand for Karnataka CM Siddaramaiah's resignation amid a Lokayukta probe into an alleged site allotment case. He accused BJP of trying to defame Congress, emphasizing that no chargesheet or conviction exists against Siddaramaiah. A Special Court has ordered an investigation into the allegations.
title: 'No question of Siddaramaiah resigning': Kharge defends K'taka CM, attacks BJP

description: A viral video shows former Indian cricket captain Mahendra Singh Dhoni riding a bike in slippers after returning from a US vacation. Fans are excited about his casual style and curious about his future with Chennai Super Kings as the IPL auction nears. CSK's CEO denied requesting Dhoni be retained as an uncapped player.
title: Viral video: Long-haired Dhoni riding bike in slippers

description: The finance ministry's pre-Budget meetings will run from October 10 to November 11, covering key ministries. Effective October 1, changes include the discontinuation of Aadhaar for PAN and ITR, higher Securities Transaction Tax, and revised TDS rates. The Direct Tax Vivad Se Vishwas Scheme seeks to settle pending tax disputes.
title: 6 income tax rules in effect before the Union budget meetings commence

description: In a UNGA speech, Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu rejected US-led ceasefire efforts with Hezbollah, emphasizing Israel's right to self-defense. He criticized global leaders' stance on Israel, highlighted potential peace deals with Saudi Arabia, and condemned the United Nations for hypocrisy. Netanyahu vowed to continue military actions until all objectives are met.
title: 'If you strike us …': Israeli PM Netanyahu gives fiery speech in UN

description: Chandra Arya, an Indian-origin Canadian MP, denounced recent demands for a fresh inquiry into the 1985 Air India bombing. He labeled these demands as efforts to promote conspiracy theories by Khalistan extremists. Arya pointed out that two previous Canadian public inquiries had already found Khalistan extremists responsible for the bombing, which killed 329 people and remains Canada's largest mass killing.
title: 'Promotion of Khalistani theories': Canada MP blasts plea on Kanishka bombing

description: Indian-Americans have significantly impacted the US unicorn ecosystem by founding or co-founding 72 of the 358 billion-dollar startups since 2018. These companies are collectively valued at over $195 billion and employ around 55,000 people. This underscores their crucial role in driving innovation and economic growth in various sectors. Indian-Americans aren’t just building companies; they’re leading them at unprecedented levels.
title: How Indian-Americans became the titans of unicorns in the US

description: Omar Abdullah rebutted BJP chief JP Nadda's comment on his mathematical abilities, asserting that common sense is more pertinent to Jammu and Kashmir elections. He criticized the central government for low voter turnout and questioned the development achievements in Jammu since the abrogation of Article 370 five years ago.
title: 'Nadda has no common sense': Omar Abdullah on union minister's remark

description: Shaheen Afridi, Pakistan’s leading fast bowler, addressed concerns from coach Gary Kirsten about his heavy workload. Kirsten noted that Afridi had bowled three times more overs than any other fast bowler globally over the past 18 months. Afridi dismissed these concerns, citing past legends like Wasim Akram and Waqar Younis who managed similar workloads.
title: 'Mental case': Shaheen roasted for Wasim, Waqar remarks

description: Maldives President Mohamed Muizzu highlighted the robust bilateral relationship with India and announced plans for a visit soon. He clarified that Maldivians are against any foreign military presence, not specifically targeting India. His administration's 'India-out' stance led to replacing Indian military personnel with civilians, causing some strain in relations following derogatory remarks against Prime Minister Narendra Modi.
title: Will visit India soon, says Maldives prez Muizzu

description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy met with former US President Donald Trump in New York, stressing the need to stop the war in Ukraine. This meeting came after Vice President Kamala Harris expressed strong support for Ukraine. Trump and Harris have differing views on US involvement as the presidential election nears.
title: 'Share a common view ...': Zelenskyy meets Trump in New York

description: Andhra Pradesh CM Chandrababu Naidu rejected Jagan Mohan Reddy's claim of being denied entry to Tirumala temple, demanding evidence. Naidu accused Reddy of misleading the public and emphasized respecting religious traditions. He announced plans for legislation requiring individuals from the same faith to work in religious institutions.
title: Tirupati laddu row: Naidu, Reddy in war of words over Tirumala visit

description: A female factory worker in Thailand's Sukhothai province died after her manager refused additional sick leave. Despite her deteriorating health, she went to work and collapsed, later dying from necrotising enterocolitis. Delta Electronics Thailand expressed condolences and is investigating the incident, which has sparked global discussions on work-life balance.
title: Factory worker dies after manager denies her sick leave

description: The income tax department will deny TDS credit and flag your ITR if it detects discrepancies between the TDS information reported in your return and that provided by the deductor. Ensuring accurate and consistent TDS data is crucial to avoid issues with the tax authorities. According to some experts, typographical errors in the PAN submitted by the taxpayer or recorded by the deductor can lead to incorrect reflection of TDS.
title: Received notice to pay additional tax? TDS claim rejection maybe cause

description: Princess Diana felt heartbroken over rumors claiming her riding instructor James Hewitt as Prince Harry's father. Her hairdresser Richard Dalton clarified that Harry was born before Diana met Hewitt and said that the red hair trait Harry got from the Spencer family. Dalton’s memoir unveils unknown aspects of Diana’s life and her relationship with Hewitt.
title: Princess Diana was heartbroken over gossip on Harry's 'biological father'

description: Oscar-winning actress Maggie Smith, known for her roles in 'Harry Potter' and 'Downton Abbey,' passed away at 89. Her sons confirmed she was with loved ones during her final moments. They thanked the hospital staff for their care and requested privacy. Smith's career spanned comedy and drama, leaving a lasting impact.
title: ‘Harry Potter’ fame Maggie Smith passes away at 89

description: Arvind Kejriwal criticized BJP for allegedly manipulating the Municipal Corporation of Delhi's election process by having an additional commissioner convene a meeting instead of the mayor. The BJP’s Sunder Singh Tanwar won a vacant seat unopposed after AAP and Congress boycotted. The standing committee now comprises 10 BJP members and eight from AAP.
title: Kejriwal, Atishi cry foul after BJP wins MCD seat; BJP hits back
Tirupati temple row: Why Reddy's religion has become a flashpoint in Andhra

description: Congress general secretary KC Venugopal called Himachal Pradesh minister Vikramaditya Singh to New Delhi regarding his remarks on eateries displaying owners' names. Venugopal stressed that no party member can oppose Congress policies. Singh claimed he was misquoted and discussed organizational activities with Venugopal, amidst protests over illegal construction in Shimla.
title: 'No minister can ...': Cong's stern words for Vikramaditya amid 'eateries diktat' row

description: The 2024 NFL season is marked by outstanding performances from key players like Dak Prescott, Lamar Jackson, and Christian McCaffrey. It also highlights impressive comebacks from injuries by athletes such as Aaron Rodgers and Joe Burrow. This blend of resilience and talent promises an engaging and competitive season.
title: NFL Players Stats (2024): Players with higher stats, rankings and more

description: The cast of Devara 1, featuring Jr NTR, Janhvi Kapoor, and Saif Ali Khan, will join The Great Indian Kapil Show 2. In a promo clip, Jr NTR humorously explains his reluctance to address Archana Puran Singh by name. The article also recalls Archana's iconic role as Miss Briganza in the film Kuch Kuch Hota Hai.
title: The Great Indian Kapil Show 2: Jr NTR reveals why he can't call Archana Puran Singh anything else but Ms Briganza

description: Sunil Gavaskar slammed the English media for their constant criticism of Indian pitches ahead of a Test series. Commentating on the second Test between India and Bangladesh, he labeled them as 'moaners' and 'crybabies.' Gavaskar praised Ashwin's performance, remembering similar complaints during an earlier match against England at Chepauk.
title: 'Moaners and crybabies': Gavaskar mocks English media

description: The BJP clinched the last vacant seat on the Municipal Corporation of Delhi's Standing Committee without opposition as AAP and Congress councillors boycotted the vote. Sunder Singh of BJP secured all 115 votes from his party, while AAP’s Nirmala Kumari got none. This gives BJP a majority with 10 members to AAP’s eight.
title: BJP wins last vacant seat of MCD's standing panel, AAP calls vote 'illegal'

description: The US Department of Justice is probing Super Micro Computer for alleged accounting irregularities reported by Hindenburg Research. This early-stage investigation has resulted in a 12% drop in the company's shares. Super Micro, a key player in AI servers, has postponed its annual report filing with the SEC to assess internal financial controls.
title: Hindenburg Research report: Super Micro Computer reportedly faces probe from US Justice Department

description: Uttar Pradesh CM Yogi Adityanath accused Congress, NC, and PDP of fostering family feuds, corruption, and terrorism for political interests. Speaking at a rally in Jammu, he contrasted the development post-abrogation of Article 370 with previous governance. He highlighted infrastructure projects like highways and educational institutions being established under the Modi government.
title: Cong, PDP & NC 'sinners' for encouraging terrorism in J&K: CM Yogi

description: Dell has announced that its global sales team must return to the office five days a week starting September 30. The company claims this move will enhance productivity and collaboration. However, many employees are unhappy with the decision, expressing their concerns on social media about potential negative impacts on morale and productivity.
title: Dell’s return to office push faces backlash from employees: “God help them…”

description: Sri Lankan batsman Kamindu Mendis has matched Don Bradman's record by reaching 1,000 Test runs in just his 13th innings. He accomplished this during the second Test against New Zealand with an unbeaten score of 182. Sri Lanka declared at a commanding total of 602 for 5 and is targeting their first series win over New Zealand since 2009.
title: New record! SL rising star now equals Don Bradman

description: The Karnataka Lokayukta Police have registered an FIR against Chief Minister Siddaramaiah for his alleged involvement in the Mysuru Urban Development Authority (MUDA) scam. This action follows a special court's order to investigate Siddaramaiah, his wife, and brother-in-law. Charges include violations under IPC and Prohibition of Benami Transaction and Land Grabbing Acts.
title: Muda case: Lokayukta police files FIR against K'taka CM Siddaramaiah

description: The opening day of the second Test saw Bangladesh at 107 for 3 when bad light stopped play. Najmul Hossain Shanto and Mominul Haque's partnership helped stabilize their innings. R Ashwin set a new record for most Test wickets in Asia by an Indian bowler, surpassing Anil Kumble.
title: 'Aage daalna padega': Pant's guidance helps Ashwin set new record

description: Odisha CM Mohan Charan Majhi recounted being asked to leave a police station by an inspector shortly before becoming CM, amid a protest over water issues. He highlighted the need for respectful treatment of citizens by police and government officials, citing another instance involving President Droupadi Murmu facing disrespect from a district collector.
title: 'Was asked to get out': Odisha CM Majhi on police station experience

description: A study from Bond University, Australia, reveals that microplastics were found in 68% of bladder cancer cases and linked to inflammation and cell damage. This finding contradicts a 2019 WHO report claiming no health threat from microplastics in drinking water. Researchers urge a re-evaluation of the public health risks posed by microplastics.
title: Microplastics in 68% bladder cases: Study challenges WHO report, raises BIG question on water safety

description: China's efforts to match US maritime power suffered a setback when its newest nuclear submarine sank at the Wuchang shipyard in Wuhan, as revealed by US officials via satellite imagery. The Zhou-class vessel, with advanced manoeuvrability, was recovered but might take months to be seaworthy again. Uncertainty surrounds potential casualties or nuclear fuel involvement, with no evidence of radiation checks by Chinese authorities. The PLA has not acknowledged the incident, raising concerns over transparency, military competence, and internal accountability. This accident is seen as a significant hindrance to China’s plans to expand its nuclear submarine fleet and maritime capabilities.
title: Another Wuhan Disaster: China's state-of-the-art submarine sank without trace, says US

description: Bad light and heavy rain stopped play before tea on day one of the second Test between India and Bangladesh in Kanpur, with Bangladesh at 107-3. Mominul Haque and Mushfiqur Rahim were batting when umpires called off play. Shakib Al Hasan may be playing his last Test match.
title: India vs Bangladesh, 2nd Test: Bad weather spoils Day 1

description: A dedicated schoolboy named Kartikey cycled 58 kilometers from Unnao to Kanpur to see his cricket idol Virat Kohli play against Bangladesh. His seven-hour journey began at 4 am and ended at Green Park Stadium by 11 am. India led the series with notable performances from Akash Deep and Ravichandran Ashwin before rain halted the match.
title: 15-year-old boy cycles 58km in 7 hours to see Kohli
'Demons in power': Jagan Reddy after cancelling Tirumala temple visit

description: Astronomers at the University of Arizona utilised the James Webb Space Telescope to study WASP-107b's atmosphere, uncovering significant east-west asymmetry. This marks a pioneering observation in space-based studies of exoplanets. The research provides valuable insights into the planet's atmospheric dynamics and composition, offering a deeper understanding of its unique characteristics.
title: James Webb telescope finds atmospheric asymmetry on exoplanet WASP-107b

description: A Bangladeshi cricket fan named Roby, dressed in a tiger costume, was allegedly heckled and taken to a medical facility during the second Test against India in Kanpur. Roby indicated he had been punched in an altercation. Authorities provided first aid before transporting him to a nearby medical facility for further treatment.
title: 2nd Test: Bangladeshi fan allegedly heckled at Green Park

description: Ravichandran Ashwin has become the leading Indian bowler with the most Test wickets in Asia, surpassing Anil Kumble's record of 419 wickets. He achieved this milestone during the second Test against Bangladesh in Kanpur by claiming his 420th wicket. This accomplishment highlights Ashwin's consistent performance and significant contribution to Indian cricket.
title: Ashwin surpasses Kumble for a big record in Test history

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi has launched three PARAM Rudra Supercomputers to enhance India's research capabilities in fields such as physics and earth science. The initiative also includes establishing 10,000 Atal Tinkering Labs in schools and increasing scholarships for STEM subjects to encourage scientific temperament among students. A Rs 1 lakh crore research fund was announced in this year's budget.
title: PM Modi inaugurates Param Rudra supercomputers: Agency behind & more

description: Keir Starmer recently met Donald Trump for a two-hour dinner in New York, aiming to build rapport with the Republican presidential candidate. Accompanied by Foreign Secretary David Lammy, Starmer discussed the US-UK relationship. While in New York, Starmer missed meeting Democratic candidate Kamala Harris, who was in Washington. He emphasised the importance of personal relationships in diplomacy. At the UN General Assembly, Starmer advocated for a more humble UK approach to international relations and urged restraint in global conflicts. He also called for permanent African representation on the UN Security Council and highlighted the catastrophic impact of ongoing global conflicts.
title: Two-hour dinner with Trump, no meet with Harris: UK PM's US trip so far

description: Kavita Dalal, known for her WWE career as Kavita Devi, is contesting the Julana seat for AAP. Facing tough rivals like Congress's Vinesh Phogat, she focuses on youth and grassroots issues. Her transition from wrestling to politics aims to bring change in Haryana. The election outcome will shape her political path.
title: Lady Khali to ‘Julana ki beti’: Ex-WWE wrestler in Haryana poll dangal

description: Congress president M Mallikarjun Kharge defends Karnataka's withdrawal of general consent for CBI investigations, highlighting past misuse allegations. He asserts that this move is within the state's rights and recalls similar actions during former CM Devraj Urs' tenure. Kharge also mentioned previous high-profile cases where the CBI declined to investigate despite their seriousness.
title: Kharge defends Karnataka govt's decision to withdraw consent given to CBI

description: A bridge collapse early Friday on the Pirpainty Dominia Chowk-Babupur route via Bakharpur road in Bihar disrupted traffic. The district administration banned two-wheelers and pedestrians from crossing bridges due to rising floodwaters. Bhagalpur DM Nawal Kishor Choudhary ordered barricades for safety, reflecting growing concerns over infrastructure integrity after recent collapses in multiple districts.
title: Another bridge collapses in Bihar's Bhagalpur

description: The Supreme Court has pulled up the air quality management commission for Delhi NCR, citing its inefficacy in tackling stubble burning and pollution. The court demanded a better compliance report and emphasized the need for grassroots-level implementation of alternative equipment to curb air pollution effectively.
title: 'On verge of serious problem': SC pulls up air quality panel for not being 'more active'

description: UK Prime Minister Keir Starmer has voiced support for India's bid to become a permanent member of the United Nations Security Council. He stressed the need for reforms to make the UNSC more representative and effective by including nations like India, Brazil, Japan, and Germany. This follows similar endorsements from US and French leaders.
title: After US & France, UK backs India's demand for permanent UNSC seat

description: The teaser for 'Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3' has been released ahead of its Diwali launch, featuring Kartik Aaryan, Vidya Balan, and Triptii Dimri. Highlights include a showdown of Vidya's iconic scene and a glimpse of "Ami Je Tomar." The film will compete with Ajay Devgn's Singham Again at the box office.
title: Kartik Aaryan, Vidya Balan steal spotlight in Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3 teaser
Watch: Disneyland arrests woman for attempting to sneak kids ticket-free

description: In his memoir 'Unleashed,' former UK PM Boris Johnson recounts his attempt to persuade Prince Harry to stay in his royal role through a 'manly pep talk' in 2020. Despite commending Harry and Meghan's contributions, Johnson found the effort futile as Harry was determined to step back from royal duties.
title: Boris Johnson gave 'manly pep talk' to Harry to stop 'Megxit'

description: American Eagle Outfitters has taken legal action against Amazon, accusing it of using Aerie trademarks in sponsored ads and search results to mislead shoppers towards counterfeit products. Filed in Manhattan federal court, the lawsuit demands an injunction and financial damages, asserting that Amazon's practices have confused consumers and tarnished Aerie's brand image.
title: American Eagle sues Amazon, claims 'unauthorised use of its trademark

description: A confrontation at Dehradun railway station turned into a communal clash involving over 100 individuals who were subsequently booked by police. The incident started with an argument between an interfaith couple, escalating into stone-pelting and vehicle damage. Police intervened to control the situation, and authorities are reviewing CCTV footage for further identification of suspects.
title: Clash at Dehradun railway station over ‘interfaith couple' from UP

description: BJP MLA Balmukund Acharya held a purification ceremony at Jaipur Municipal Corporation Heritage to combat corruption and welcome ex-Congress councillors into the BJP. Utilizing 'Gangajal' and 'gaumutra', Acharya sought to cleanse officials and councillors, heralding a fresh start for the corporation under newly appointed mayor Kusum Yadav.
title: BJP MLA uses gaumutra for 'purification' of turncoat Congress councillors

description: A video featuring an Indian techie paying Rs 99,000 rent for a single room in Toronto has gained attention online. Despite earning $100,000 annually, she expressed dissatisfaction with her salary due to rising living costs and inflation.
title: Indian techie says Rs 60 lakh salary not enough to survive in Canada

description: Virat Kohli's extraordinary fame was evident at Kanpur's Green Park Stadium during the second Test between India and Bangladesh. Although he has played few matches there, his impact remains strong. A viral video shows a ground staff member attempting to touch his feet, underscoring Kohli's iconic status in Indian cricket.
title: Watch: Green Park ground staff touches Virat Kohli's feet

description: Shigeru Ishiba has won the leadership race of Japan's ruling Liberal Democratic Party, positioning him as the next prime minister. The 67-year-old defeated economic security minister Sanae Takaichi in a runoff. Known for his progressive stance within the conservative party, Ishiba plans to boost real wages and reduce reliance on nuclear energy.
title: Who is Shigeru Ishiba? Japan's next prime minister

description: NASA has released live footage of Hurricane Helene, which is set to hit Florida's eastern coast tonight as a Category 4 storm. The hurricane is predicted to cause catastrophic storm surges and severe flooding. Many are already without power, and officials are urging residents to prepare for extremely dangerous conditions.
title: Watch: Nasa shares footage of Hurricane Helene's landfall from space station

description: On day one of the second Test at Kanpur, India's video referral reversed an on-field umpire's not-out call on Akash Deep’s LBW appeal against Bangladesh’s Shadman Islam. Rohit Sharma’s shocked reaction went viral as the review supported the bowler, dismissing Shadman. India lead the two-match series 1-0 following their victory in Chennai.
title: Rohit Sharma's jaw-dropping reaction on DRS call goes viral

description: Shigeru Ishiba won the Liberal Democratic Party leadership election with 215 votes and is set to become Japan's next prime minister. Defeating Sanae Takaichi who secured 194 votes, Ishiba emphasizes his experience in tackling social issues. The LDP has governed Japan nearly uninterrupted for decades, often overshadowing opposition parties.
title: Shigeru Ishiba to become Japan's next prime minister

description: Diwali, one of the most significant Hindu festivals, will be celebrated on October 31, 2024. The main event, Laxmi Puja, will take place after sunset. The festival spans five days starting with Dhanteras on October 29 and concluding with Bhai Dooj on November 3. Diwali symbolizes the triumph of light over darkness.
title: When is Deepawali? All you need to know about this festival

description: Dwayne Bravo has been appointed as the mentor for Kolkata Knight Riders following his retirement from cricket. With a career spanning 18 years and titles in IPL, PSL, and Big Bash leagues, Bravo brings vast experience to KKR. CEO Venky Mysore highlighted Bravo's drive to win. Bravo is eager to mentor the next generation of players.
title: Dwayne Bravo replaces Gautam Gambhir as KKR's new mentor
Apple announces date of its Diwali sale

description: China's newest nuclear-powered attack submarine, identified as a Zhou-class submarine, sank at a pier during construction between May and June. This incident occurred at the Wuchang shipyard, raising concerns about the quality of China's military equipment and training standards. The extent of damage, cause of sinking, and whether nuclear fuel was onboard remain unknown.
title: China's newest nuclear-powered submarine sinks at Wuhan port

description: The Israeli military intercepted a missile launched from Yemen, heightening fears of wider Middle East conflict amid ongoing strikes on Hezbollah in Lebanon. The missile was downed outside Israel’s borders without direct impacts. This follows the Huthi rebels' support for Hezbollah and Israel’s rejection of a US-led ceasefire proposal.
title: Footage shows Israel intercepting Yemen missile with the 'arrow' amid sirens

description: Sanae Takaichi, a protégé of former Prime Minister Shinzo Abe, is aiming to be Japan's first female prime minister. Known for her conservative stance on social issues, she focuses on economic growth and national security. Her visits to Tokyo’s Yasukuni Shrine have sparked protests from South Korea and China due to historical wartime actions.
title: Who is Sanae Takaichi? Japan's potential first female prime minister

description: A Bengaluru executive was scammed out of Rs 51 lakh in a 'digital arrest' scheme. Posing as officials from FedEx, Mumbai police, and RBI, fraudsters convinced her that her Aadhaar details were used for illegal activities. They manipulated her into transferring money over a ten-hour period without food or water.
title: Bengaluru-based MNC exec loses Rs 51L in ‘digital arrest’ scam that lasted 10 hrs
Watch: Biden mistakenly calls senator JD Vance 'secretary' in latest gaffe

description: A viral parody song targeting Donald Trump's assertion that immigrants are eating cats and dogs in Ohio has reached over nine million views on YouTube within 12 days. The revenue generated will support Clark County SPCA's efforts to find homes for stray animals in Springfield, Ohio. The artist believes music can unite people, especially when it involves animals.
title: 'Eating the cats' viral parody song on Trump gets over 9M views

description: Virat Kohli has been named in Delhi's Ranji Trophy probables list, rekindling memories of his early career. Starting in the 2006-07 season, Kohli faced challenges but excelled with notable performances. A defining moment was scoring 90 runs against Karnataka just after his father's death, showcasing his commitment and mental fortitude which propelled him to international success. Kohli last participated in a Ranji Trophy match for the Delhi team in 2012 in Ghaziabad against Uttar Pradesh.
title: 'I won't pay a penny...': When Virat Kohli was dropped from Delhi team

description: Mukti Ranjan Ray, suspected of murdering Mahalakshmi in Bengaluru, was found dead by suicide in Odisha. He allegedly killed her, dismembered her body, and stored the parts in a refrigerator. His brother disclosed that Mukti planned to dispose of the remains later but ended his life due to guilt and depression.
title: Mahalakshmi murder case: 'Killer planned to get rid of body parts after 2-3 months'
Flight to China lands in Kolkata as Iraqi girl falls ill on board, dies

description: Green Park Stadium in Kanpur may not host more international cricket matches due to subpar facilities, with the BCCI favoring Lucknow's Ekana Stadium and a new venue in Varanasi. Currently, UPCA is inviting families of martyred soldiers and local children to attend the ongoing Test match as part of a special initiative.
title: Green Park Stadium stares at an uncertain future

description: A viral video of Bihar job aspirants being assaulted in West Bengal has led to political backlash. The students were in Siliguri for a Staff Selection Commission exam and faced harassment for not being local residents. Rajat Bhattacharya, an activist of Bangla Pokkho, has been detained by the police for questioning.
title: Bihar job aspirants assaulted in West Bengal, video sparks massive row

description: Palestinian President Mahmoud Abbas appealed to the UN General Assembly for urgent intervention to end the conflict between Israel and Hamas in Gaza. He highlighted the severe destruction in Gaza, calling for a ceasefire, humanitarian access, and Israeli withdrawal. Abbas also stressed that the Palestinian Authority should manage Gaza's borders and promised elections after peace is achieved.
title: 'Gaza no longer fit for life': Palestinian President paints grim picture at UN

description: In the final of the MCC Weekdays Bash XIX, Rabdan Cricket Club's Kashif Muhammad and Aerovisa Cricket's Nasir Ali were involved in a fist-fight. The incident began with Ali giving Kashif an aggressive send-off, which escalated into a physical altercation. Teammates and umpires intervened to separate the two players.
title: Cricketers come to blows, bats used as swords! - Watch

description: Several Iranian nationals have been indicted for hacking former President Donald Trump’s 2024 campaign, sharing stolen material with Biden’s re-election team. US authorities confirmed Iran's involvement in the cyber attack. The DOJ may announce charges soon, highlighting Iran's aggressive attempts to influence the election due to its national security interests.
title: Iranian nationals charged over hacking of Trump’s 2024 US presidential campaign

description: The Indian men's hockey team players, who were part of the bronze medal-winning Olympic campaigns in Tokyo and Paris, experienced an awkward moment when fans at an airport ignored them to take selfies with Dolly chaiwala. Star midfielder Hardik Singh recounted this incident, underscoring the team's accomplishments and stressing how vital public appreciation is for athletes' morale.
title: Fans ask Dolly chaiwala for selfies, ignore India's Paris Oly medallists

description: A Pocso court in Kolkata has sentenced a gas delivery agent to death for the rape and murder of his landlord's seven-year-old daughter, committed in March last year. Despite claiming he acted on advice from a tantrik, evidence proved otherwise. Crucial testimony came from his pregnant wife.
title: Kolkata man murders 7-yr-old on occultist's advice, gets death penalty

description: Shankaracharya Swami Avimukteshwaranand Saraswati's campaign advocating a ban on cow slaughter faced roadblocks in Arunachal Pradesh and Nagaland. Authorities in both states denied him entry, citing concerns about public unrest and constitutional provisions. The seer was asked to return to Guwahati after being stopped at airports in both states.
title: Seer on cow protection mission denied Arunachal, Nagaland entry

description: Manipur's government has retracted an earlier intelligence report claiming 900 Kuki militants infiltrated from Myanmar. New police inputs suggest Kuki National Army cadres might escort arms, ammunition, and drugs from Myanmar. Officials clarified that the initial report couldn't be substantiated and assured the public there's no immediate threat, urging calm.
title: Manipur retracts intel on militants as report raises info leak stink

description: Mira Murati has decided to resign from her role as chief technology officer at OpenAI to focus on personal exploration. CEO Sam Altman expressed his gratitude for her contributions. Additionally, two other top executives, Bob McGrew and Barret Zoph, are also leaving the company independently and amicably, according to Altman.
title: 'I'm stepping away because ... ': Why Mira Murati quit as CTO Of OpenAI

description: Joe Biden signed a stopgap spending bill to avert an immediate government shutdown, keeping the US government operational until mid-December. The bill maintains current funding levels for agencies and provides additional funds for the Secret Service. Biden highlighted support for national defense, veterans, and working families while opposing IRS budget cuts targeting wealthy tax evaders.
title: 'To keep govt open': What is stopgap spending bill signed by Biden

description: Drone footage from the Israeli Defence Forces captures the killing of Muhammad Hussein Srour, a senior Hezbollah commander, in Beirut. Known for his role in developing Hezbollah's UAV capabilities and leading strategic operations against Israel, Srour's death further escalates tensions between Israel and Hezbollah following the October 7 Hamas attack.
title: Watch: How Israel 'eliminated' Hezbollah commander who developed UAVs in Lebanon

description: The finance ministry of India reports solid macroeconomic stability marked by steady growth in investment, employment, and inflation trends. However, global economic uncertainties and potential stock market corrections present challenges. Low oil prices benefit the economy while increased public expenditure is expected to drive further growth. GDP growth for FY25 is projected at 6.5-7%.
title: Economy on track for 6.5-7% growth in FY25: Finance minister

description: An explosion at a police station in Pakistan's Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province has led to the death of one child and injuries to 25 people, primarily police officers. The blast is believed to have been caused by a short circuit. Rescue efforts are ongoing, with injured individuals transported to the district headquarters hospital for medical care.
title: At least 1 child killed, 25 cops injured in Pakistan police station blast

description: California Governor Gavin Newsom signed a law formally apologizing for slavery and its effects on Black Americans. This is part of a series of reparations bills aimed at addressing racial disparities. Although no direct payment legislation was passed, Newsom approved a budget with up to $12 million for reparations legislation.
title: California apologizes for slavery, its effects on Black Americans

description: Hardik Singh asserts that India's hockey players surpass cricketers in fitness based on the Yo-Yo Intermittent Recovery test, highlighting that even the Indian goalkeeper has a score of 21 versus top cricketers' scores of around 19 or 20. The Indian men's hockey team will compete against Germany in a two-match series in Delhi on October 23-24.
title: ​Hardik's massive clam! Indian hockey players fitter than cricketers

description: The CBI court in Kolkata has noted that the charges against former RG Kar principal Sandip Ghosh and ex-Tala police officer Abhijit Mandal are serious enough to potentially warrant capital punishment. Both individuals remain in custody as investigations into the RG Kar rape-and-murder case continue, with irregularities found in the post-mortem process.

description: The ministerial panel on GST rationalisation has discussed proposals for adjusting rates on over 100 items and merging the 12% and 18% slabs. The fitment committee will analyse the impact, potentially reducing rates for common goods and increasing them for luxury items. Further discussions are scheduled in Delhi later this month.
title: Ministerial panel looks to rework GST rates on over 100 items

description: Swiggy has filed for an IPO estimated at $1.2 billion, which could increase to $1.4 billion following a shareholder meeting. The company intends to raise Rs 3,750 crore through new shares and the rest from an offer-for-sale by existing investors. The IPO might be timed with Diwali festivities in November.

description: President Joe Biden has signed an executive order aimed at reducing gun violence by targeting 3D-printed guns and machine guns. The order calls for universal background checks, safe firearm storage, and improved active shooter drills in schools. Vice President Kamala Harris stressed the need to reinstate the assault weapons ban during her first gun-related event with Biden.

Australian cricketers Mitchell Marsh and Travis Head praised his aggressive approach and resilience.
